      <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-wine-700 mb-1">1. Cristom Mt. Jefferson Cuvée</h3>
      <p class="text-sm text-gray-600 mb-2">Eola-Amity Hills, Oregon</p>
      <p class="text-gray-700 text-sm">A strong holiday Pinot Noir because it has enough lift for turkey and cranberry sauce, but still enough savory depth for stuffing and gravy. This is the best one-bottle answer for a mixed plate.</p>
